comment:
* Holds the characteristics of the reflecting plane that a satellite signal has bounced from.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: mLatitudeDegrees
variables.comment: Represents latitude in degrees of the reflecting plane

variables.name: mLongitudeDegrees
variables.comment: Represents longitude in degrees of the reflecting plane.

variables.name: mAltitudeMeters
variables.comment:
* Represents altitude in meters above the WGS 84 reference ellipsoid of the reflection point in
     * the plane

variables.name: mAzimuthDegrees
variables.comment: Represents azimuth clockwise from north of the reflecting plane in degrees.

methods.name: public double getLatitudeDegrees()
methods.comment: Gets the latitude in degrees of the reflecting plane.

methods.name: public double getLongitudeDegrees()
methods.comment: Gets the longitude in degrees of the reflecting plane.

methods.name: public double getAltitudeMeters()
methods.comment:
* Gets the altitude in meters above the WGS 84 reference ellipsoid of the reflecting point
     * within the plane

methods.name: public double getAzimuthDegrees()
methods.comment: Gets the azimuth clockwise from north of the reflecting plane in degrees.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel parcel, int flags)
